		<div id="System_Circuit_Diagram">
			<div class="content1">How to Read System Circuit Diagram<img title="Print" name='howto05.pdf' /></div>
			<div class="content4">The circuit diagram is designed so the current flows from the top of the diagram (power source) to the bottom of </div>
			<div class="content4">the diagram (ground) as if giving an image of water flow.</div>
			<div class="content5">[A]: Fuse No.</div>
			<div class="content5">[B]: Circuit jumping point / direction</div>
			<div class="note">NOTE
				<HR/>
					The circuit continues to the same symbol with the opposite direction within the page.<BR/>
					You will find the other symbol in the direction of the arrow.
				<HR/>
			</div>
			<div class="content5">[C]: Wire color</div>
			<div class="content5">[D]: Shield wire</div>
			<div class="content5">[E]: Ground point</div>
			<div class="content5">[F]: "From" or "To" (With ID letter (s))</div>
			<div class="content5">[G]: Specification variation</div>
			<div class="note">NOTE
				<HR/>
					The white arrow between A and B means "or".
				<HR/>
			</div>
			<div class="content5">[H]: "From" (With ID letter (s))</div>
			<div class="content5">[I]: "To" (With ID letter (s))</div>
			<div class="content5">[J]: Terminal No.</div>
			<div class="content5">[K]: Connector code</div>
			<div class="content5">[L]: Symbol mark</div>
			<div class="content5">[M]: "SEE" mark</div>
			<embed width="971" height="1158" src="../swf/English/I1RD00000011.swf"></embed>
